# === Confidentiality guardrails (this repo is PUBLIC) ===
# One vault: public content is tracked & pushed; private / home-lab / security
# notes live in the gitignored paths below — local-only, never pushed. Clients
# live in Hudu. These patterns are the control that keeps the private tier out of
# the public remote: file sensitive notes under private/ (etc.) and they stay local.
private/
clients/
client-*/
*.private.md
*.secret.md
secrets/
**/secrets/
heimdall-stack/
infra-inventory/

# Secrets / credentials
*.key
*.pem
*.crt
*.p12
*.pfx
*.env
.env
.env.*
*credentials*
*.kdbx
id_rsa*
id_ed25519*
*.ovpn

# Obsidian workspace state (keep config/, drop volatile caches)
.obsidian/workspace.json
.obsidian/workspace-mobile.json
.obsidian/cache
.trash/

# Local retrieval index / embeddings (regenerated locally)
.retrieve/
*.duckdb
*.sqlite3
embeddings/

# claude-obsidian retrieval pipeline — vendored locally, not published.
# The public repo stays a pure knowledge vault; this tooling + its generated
# index live on disk only and are regenerated via bin/setup-retrieve.sh.
scripts/
bin/
.vault-meta/

# Quartz publish pipeline — deploy artifacts staged locally, applied to the
# builder LXC + thallium. Not part of the published knowledge vault.
deploy/

# Local planning (kept on disk, not published)
tasks/

# OS / editor junk
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
*.swp
*~
.idea/
.vscode/
